Billiatt Wilderness Protection Area
South Australia

Billiatt Wilderness Protection Area
Nearest town or city Alawoona[2]
Coordinates 35°00′50″S 140°23′25″E﻿ / ﻿35.013867266°S 140.390333169°E﻿ / -35.013867266; 140.390333169Coordinates: 35°00′50″S 140°23′25″E﻿ / ﻿35.013867266°S 140.390333169°E﻿ / -35.013867266; 140.390333169[1]

Billiatt Wilderness Protection Area is a protected area located about 30 kilometres (19 miles) north of Lameroo in South Australia.[6][3]

The wilderness protection area occupies in land in the gazetted localities of Billiatt, Lameroo and Sandalwood.[2]

The wilderness protection area was proclaimed under the Wilderness Protection Act 1992 on 24 July 2008 on land excised from the Billiatt Conservation Park.[7]

It is classified as an IUCN Category Ib protected area.[1]
